ound filling, forming a cylinder shape, keeping the filling at the top of the dumpling uncovered. Tap the bottom of the dumplings lightly on a flat work surface to ensure they stand up straight. Place 10 dumplings into Varoma dish and 10 dumplings on Varoma tray."},{"content":"Place water into mixing bowl, place Varoma into position, secure Varoma lid and steam <b>15 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<b>. Serve dumplings warm, garnished with fish roe (optional)."}],"hintsAndTricks":["To save time, you can use pre-made wonton wrappers in this recipe.","You can replace the small shrimp with peeled prawns, cut into small pieces, if preferred.","These dumplings are usually served with a dipping sauce; often a mixture of soy sauce, sesame oil and black vinegar.","<strong>Coloured sui mai:<\/strong> To make yellow sui mai wrappers, add 10 g ground turmeric to the dough when adding flour. To make green sui mai wrappers, replace the water with 50 g spinach juice."],"basicInfo":["medium","40m","1h","20 portions"]}